    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "\"Categorical syllogisms\" are so called because they are made up of categorical statements. A statement is a sentence that is either true or false, and a categorical one is a statement that relates two types or categories of thing. There are four types of categorical statement:",
        "spans": [
