      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "These four types of statement are called A, E, I, and O type statements, as indicated. The variables, S and P, are place-holders for terms which pick out a category of thing. As you can see, each type of categorical statement asserts a different logical relation between two categories.",
        "spans": [
          {
            "start": 41,
            "end": 42,
            "type": "strong"
          },
          {
            "start": 44,
            "end": 45,
