      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "The notion of distribution plays a role in some of the syllogistic fallacies: the terms in a categorical statement are said to be \"distributed\" or \"undistributed\" in that statement, depending on what type of statement it is, and whether the term is the subject or predicate term. Specifically, the subject term is distributed in the A and E type statements, and the predicate term is distributed in the E and O type statements. The other terms are undistributed.",
